                <div class="frequency-info">
                    <span class="status-code-mini server-error">500 Server Error</span>
                    <span class="frequency-text">Server problem</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="http-headers">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> HTTP Headers: Extra Information</h3>
        <p>Headers are like metadata - extra information about the request or response.</p>
        
        <div class="headers-grid">
            <div class="header-type">
                <h4>Request Headers</h4>
                <p>What client sends to server:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>User-Agent:</strong> What browser/device you're using</li>
                    <li><strong>Accept:</strong> What formats you can understand</li>
                    <li><strong>Cookie:</strong> Your login/session information</li>
                    <li><strong>Authorization:</strong> Your login credentials</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="header-type">
                <h4>Response Headers</h4>
                <p>What server sends back:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Content-Type:</strong> What type of data is returned</li>
                    <li><strong>Set-Cookie:</strong> Save login/session info</li>
                    <li><strong>Cache-Control:</strong> How long to store the data</li>
                    <li><strong>Location:</strong> Where to redirect to</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="interactive-game">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-gamepad"></i> Status Code Detective</h3>
        <p>What status code would you get in these situations?</p>
        
        <div class="game-scenarios">
            <div class="game-scenario" data-correct="403">
                <p>You try to visit "facebook.com/profile/secret" but you're not logged in</p>
                <div class="game-options">
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="403">403 Forbidden</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="404">404 Not Found</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="200">200 OK</button>
                </div>
                <div class="game-feedback"></div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="game-scenario" data-correct="200">
                <p>You successfully load the YouTube homepage</p>
                <div class="game-options">
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="200">200 OK</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="500">500 Error</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="301">301 Moved</button>
                </div>
                <div class="game-feedback"></div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="game-scenario" data-correct="404">
                <p>You type "amazon.com/product-that-doesnt-exist"</p>
                <div class="game-options">
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="404">404 Not Found</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="200">200 OK</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary game-btn" data-answer="403">403 Forbidden</button>
                </div>
                <div class="game-feedback"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="http-cookies">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-cookie-bite"></i> Cookies: How Websites Remember You</h3>
        
        <div class="cookie-explanation">
            <div class="cookie-step">
                <div class="cookie-number">1</div>
                <div class="cookie-content">
                    <h5>First Visit</h5>
                    <p>You visit a website for the first time</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="cookie-arrow">→</div>
            
            <div class="cookie-step">
                <div class="cookie-number">2</div>
                <div class="cookie-content">
                    <h5>Server Sends Cookie</h5>
                    <p>Server says: "Remember this ID: user123"</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="cookie-arrow">→</div>
            
            <div class="cookie-step">
                <div class="cookie-number">3</div>
                <div class="cookie-content">
                    <h5>Browser Stores It</h5>
                    <p>Your browser saves: "facebook.com = user123"</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="cookie-arrow">→</div>
            
            <div class="cookie-step">
                <div class="cookie-number">4</div>
                <div class="cookie-content">
                    <h5>Next Visit</h5>
                    <p>You say: "Hey Facebook, I'm user123!"</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="cookie-arrow">→</div>
            
            <div class="cookie-step">
                <div class="cookie-number">5</div>
                <div class="cookie-content">
                    <h5>Website Remembers</h5>
                    <p>Facebook knows it's you and shows your profile</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="key-points">
        <h3>Key Points to Remember - Part 2</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Status Codes:</strong> 2xx (Success), 3xx (Redirect), 4xx (Your fault), 5xx (Server fault)</li>
            <li><strong>200 OK:</strong> Everything worked perfectly</li>
            <li><strong>404 Not Found:</strong> Most famous error - page doesn't exist</li>
            <li><strong>Headers:</strong> Extra information in requests/responses</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> How websites remember you between visits</li>
            <li><strong>Stateless:</strong> HTTP doesn't remember previous requests (cookies help with this)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("HttpPart1", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-outline-primary ajax-link">← HTTP Part 1</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("ClientSide", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-primary ajax-link">Next: Client-Side Communication →</a>
    </div>
</div>

